'''''The Height''''' ([[Russian_language|Russian]]: [[:ru:%D0%92%D1%8B%D1%81%D0%BE%D1%82%D0%B0 (%D1%84%D0%B8%D0%BB%D1%8C%D0%BC)|<U+0412><U+044B><U+0441><U+043E><U+0442><U+0430>]], [[Transliteration|Translit.]]: Vysota) is a [[1957_in_film|1957]] Soviet drama film produced at [[Mosfilm]] and directed by [[Aleksandr_Zarkhi|Aleksander Zarkhi]] after the same name novel written by [[:ru:%D0%92%D0%BE%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%B1%D1%8C%D1%91%D0%B2, %D0%95%D0%B2%D0%B3%D0%B5%D0%BD%D0%B8%D0%B9 %D0%97%D0%B0%D1%85%D0%B0%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%B2%D0%B8%D1%87|Evgeny Vorobyov]].
